column3: Dmitar has exciting news to share from the southern front.
A Resistance rank of <Value>IntegerParameter(1)</Value> is required to proceed with this quest.
Blade <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,2)/>! We received word from the field─the Empire's forces have fallen back!
In fact, our troops have pushed forward far enough as to claim an enemy encampment near the southern entrenchment.
My commanding officer has instructed me to give you a brief tour of the site at your earliest convenience. I will await you there.
Welcome to Olana's Stand. If you wish to travel between here and Utya's Aegis, feel free to use that aetheryte shard over there. I would suggest attuning to it before you leave.
And one last thing: while we've made great strides in our fight against the Empire, there's still much to be done before we can retake Castrum Lacus Litore.
I expect the enemy will only grow more determined as we advance forward, but we must press on. For Bozja!
The Resistance front line advances, allowing you to participate in new skirmishes and critical engagements.
The next quest can be accepted by speaking with Mikoto after reaching Resistance rank <Value>IntegerParameter(1)</Value> or higher.
